_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating decision action**\\n\\nI need to be careful not to overdo it. The user asked for a \\\"Return decision\\\" action which could be either no_action or advisory. It seems \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" is likely meant for guidance. I'll consider that the Forge workflow may use this JSON to apply a deterministic setup before generating and passing on guidance. If I choose no_action, the agent might miss out on a useful JDK25 warning. Let’s make sure to weigh these options carefully!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL has no extra service or non-transitive dependency requirement, but meaningful tests that exercise its reflective/JDK9+ access paths need JVM module-opening setup documented by the artifact's own JDK17+ test profile.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure OGNL tests that exercise reflection, JDK9+ accessible-object handling, or expression compilation with test JVM args `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`. Do not rely on `--illegal-access=permit` on JDK 25. If testing OGNL security-manager behavior, set and restore `ognl.security.manager` inside the test and guard for JDKs where `System.setSecurityManager` is unsupported.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The resolved artifact already brings `org.javassist:javassist:3.29.0-GA` transitively; adding it explicitly is unnecessary unless Gradle resolution proves otherwise.\",\n    \"The observed JDK 25 java-run failure appears to be a behavioral/test assertion issue, not a missing dependency or Docker setup issue.\",\n    \"SecurityManager-focused coverage is brittle on modern JDKs and should not be the only coverage path.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_089a3702d458b2c4016a3f9d80c3fc8195905080ce998acefe\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"in